Rating: 4
Wow - so flavorful for something so simple! My husband said it was his favorite soup I've ever made (and I make soup about once a week!). My only changes were to use veggie broth instead of water, 2/3 cup skim milk + 1/3 low-fat buttermilk for the milk (b/c that's what I had on hand). Added a splash of white wine at the end and way more salt, and used an immersion blender but left it slightly chunky. Huge flavor for so few ingredients! The fresh dill really makes it. Next time I think I'll saute some caraway seeds with the veggies as well.

