Rating: 3
I took the advice of previous reviewers to use chicken broth instead of water. I reduced the amount of butter to 2 T. - it's plenty to saute the vegetables. I deglazed the pot with chicken broth before I added the potatoes and used an immersion blender but left it a little chunky. I used 3/4 cup of 2% milk and 1/4 cup of half/half. At the end I stirred in about 1/4 cup of white wine and a generous splash of white wine vinegar to give the acid that it did seem to need. The wine gives a nice aroma that adds to the richness of the soup. Delicious!

